      "authorityLevel": "primary_regulatory",
      "authorityKey": "ndow",
      "retrievedDate": "2026-07-02",
      "quotedText": "The primary fishery consists of rainbow trout and channel catfish, with catchable sizes of both species being stocked seasonally. Bluegill, redear sunfish, black crappie, and largemouth bass also occur and spawn naturally. Stocking Updates (selected): 381 Channel Catfish, 19 in, 06-13-2026; 476 Channel Catfish, 17.5 in, 05-23-2026; 1890 Rainbow Trout, 8.9 in, 03-03-2026; 1215 Rainbow Trout, 8.5 in, 12-22-2025; 1045 Rainbow trout, 10.6 in, 01-11-2023"
    },
